25 November 2008The Minister of Health, Ms Barbara Hogan, together with World Health Organisation Representative in South Africa, Dr Stella Anyangwe will brief the media on the government response to the cholera situation in South Africa.The briefing will take place as follows:Date: Wednesday, 26 November 2008 Time: 14:00 Venue: Room 153, Union Buildings, PretoriaNote: There will be a link-up to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape TownEnquiries Fidel Hadebe (Pretoria) Cell: 079 517 3333Harold Maloka (Pretoria) Cell: 082 847 9799Colin Cruywagen (Cape Town) Cell: 082 377 9916Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)